NIO support file IO and accessing default file system.



Path class apis followed by File class apis
    Std file io apis such as check, delete, copy, move are explained.
    Metadata of file File IO and directory IO


Path
    File paths, tree structure

  Some file systems support the notion of symbolic links.
  A symbolic link is referred to as a symlink or a soft link.
   symlink is special file that serves as reference to other file.


Path object contain file name, directory list used to construct file path.
used to examine, locate and manipulate files.



 Path instance contain info used to specify location of file or directory.

